                            كَذْبَانُونَةٌ
                         [Pers. كَدْبَانو] An intelligent housewife, who is a good manager. (K, art. هلج;
but omitted in some copies.)


                            كَظَائِمُ
                         [pl. of كِظَامَةٌ] Subterranean conduits
for water. (TA in art. قنو.)
